  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Refining Image Generation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on generating realistic mockups, specifically for an Ableton Live AI assistant VST plugin. The goal is a sleek, futuristic chat interface, with a dark UI accented by neon cyan and emerald green. I\'m keeping the image count in check and working on clean naming conventions.\n\n\n**Generating Studio Assets**\n\nI\'ve decided to create two high-quality assets in parallel using `default_api:generate_image`. One will be a futuristic plugin GUI (`alan_plugin_gui`) within Ableton Live, featuring a dark mode, neon green accents, and a glowing chat window. The other is a photorealistic, futuristic music producer studio at night (`producer_studio_night`), complete with neon lights, modular synths, and Ableton Live displayed. I\'m excited to see these visuals come to life.\n\n\n**Inspecting Setup & Assets**\n\nI\'m now diving into the setup, specifically reading `metadata.json` to prepare for its update, ensuring the app name is \"ALAN Ableton AI Assistant\". I\'ll also be reviewing `package.json` to confirm and assess any packages. Next, I plan to thoroughly inspect the file structure, checking for missing parts or elements, focusing on the configuration of components.\n\n\n"
