  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Adapting to Resource Constraints**\n\nI\'ve hit a resource quota error with the `generate_image` tool, but it\'s no problem. My plan now is to use the `https://picsum.photos/seed/test/{width}/{height}` fallback as the instructions suggest for placeholder images when there are no other assets available. Alternatively, I am considering designing the UI natively in Tailwind CSS, which opens up interesting design possibilities.\n\n\n**Designing a Superior UI**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in designing a sleek Ableton Live simulator UI using Tailwind CSS. The dark theme with glowing accents fits the user\'s aesthetic perfectly, and I\'m planning smooth, interactive animations using Framer Motion. I\'ve begun visualizing the layout, focusing on a track list with state indicators, volume faders, and active MIDI clip representations. The goal is to create a responsive, animated, and interactive mock-up of the DAW.\n\n\n**Visualizing Plugin Integration**\n\nI\'m now focusing on integrating the ALAN plugin GUI within the Ableton Live simulator. My main concept is to include an audio waveform timeline within the clip grid and have the ALAN plugin GUI window on the right (or docked). This window will include a chat header, scroll area, and input box. I aim to make this interactive by letting users click on suggested AI commands or enter their own. Upon selecting/submitting a command, I\'m planning realistic chat exchanges and dynamic UI changes in response.\n\n\n**Refining Scroll Integration**\n\nI\'m now refining the single-scroll design approach. The homepage will be an interactive showcase, with elements changing dynamically as the user scrolls. I\'m imagining a display of sidechain routing and volume meter activity with interactive features, and suggestions like \"Apply dark reverb to SFX Track\" dynamically updating elements. The interaction should feel incredibly modern, and not rely on static image files. I\'m focusing on the Homepage, Docs, About, and Support pages, all within a cohesive single-scroll framework.\n\n\n**Crafting Unified Navigation**\n\nI\'m now integrating a sticky navigation header, inspired by futuristic product presentations. It will track the active section and use smooth scrolling. The layout will include the ALAN logo, and links to [ALAN], [Docs], [About], [Support]. I\'m also planning a dark, immersive UI with a deep obsidian space grid background and glowing accents. I\'m importing Space Grotesk and JetBrains Mono fonts and styling modern custom scrollbars and gradients. The ALAN homepage will feature an interactive DAW simulator filling the screen.\n\n\n**Developing Interactive Mockups**\n\nI\'m now focusing on interactive mockups for each page. The homepage is becoming a dynamic Live-Simulator Canvas that models DAW tracks, active waveforms, and a floating ALAN VST window. Tracks, meters, and notes will dynamically respond to commands! The docs page will feature a navigation sidebar and interactive code snippets in JetBrains Mono. I\'m planning an interactive timeline for the about page to explain the architecture, and a live command center terminal with a query box for the support page.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 9
      nanos: 600329303
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
