  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the DAW Simulator**\n\nI\'m making excellent headway on designing the DAWSimulator component. My current focus is on visual design! I\'m aiming for a beautiful replica of Ableton Live\'s UI, including track views, faders, meters, waveform cells, a playhead scrubber, BPM counter, and a MIDI grid. It is an ambitious project, but my goal is to make it a marvel of frontend design!\n\n\n**Defining the ALAN AI**\n\nNow, I\'m focusing on the ALAN AI\'s operational design within the DAWSimulator. I\'m building its core data structures, including mock tracks and state variables like BPM and active action. I\'m also planning the `terminalMessageScroll` log and `chatInput` state, which will enable user interaction. Finally, the play state will animate the tracks!\n\n\n**Animating the Visuals**\n\nI\'m now implementing preset animations. \"Quantize Synth MIDI\" will grid-align MIDI notes with green sparks. \"Configure Sidechain Ducking\" will draw a pulsating blue waveform, affecting the volume slider. \"Insert Atmospheric Reverb\" adds a glowing pink haze on the vocal track. \"Accelerate Tempo\" will flash the BPM counter cyan as it increases.\n\n\n**Accelerating Visual Feedback**\n\nI\'ve significantly increased the tempo visualization; drum clip waveforms now roll and pulse much faster, providing more dynamic feedback. The AI, ALAN, has set the global BPM to 138, and is also logging the synchronization and scaling operations. I\'ve also incorporated a neural melody generator; cascading MIDI note squares now appear on Track 1, accompanied by yellow/green sparkles, and AI logs the melody generation process.\nI\'m also planning to implement a small heuristic response generator so that the chat bar can provide witty music-producer terminology based on whatever keywords are typed. I will focus on implementing precise CSS rendering of the DAW. I\'m focusing on the implementation by drafting `src/components/DAWSimulator.tsx`. I have selected many icons from `lucide-react` to use.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 59
      nanos: 312194105
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
