  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Core Components**\n\nI\'ve made good progress! I have all the standard components defined: Navigation, DAWSimulator, DocsSection, AboutSection, and SupportSection. Now, I need to read `src/App.tsx` carefully. I will rewrite it to integrate these components in a way that makes sense.\n\n\n**Visualizing Dynamic Interactions**\n\nI\'m now focused on the interactive scrolling. I\'ve decided on a dark sci-tech aesthetic for the full-screen homepage. I\'m building an elegant Scroll-Spy to observe scroll coordinates, which I\'ll use to create real-time interactive states. I plan to dynamically link the Navigation highlights to the visible elements and introduce scrolling effects like background glow/color shifts and fading entry cards using Framer Motion. I\'m also adding glowing ambient spot overlays.\n\n\n**Refining Aesthetic Details**\n\nI\'m now diving deep into the visual details! I want to achieve a \"futuristic, next-era, premium storytelling vibe.\" I\'m planning to introduce a purple glow effect that changes dynamically as the user scrolls, which is crucial to the design. I\'m reviewing the required sections to keep the plan precise: ALAN (hero), Docs, About, and Support. I\'ll craft a new `src/App.tsx`, and I\'m ready to carefully refine the visuals.\n\n\n**Designing Hero Layout**\n\nI\'m now sketching the hero section, incorporating \"AN ASSISTANT TO YOUR IMAGINATION\" as the display typography, with the title \"ALAN AI: The Intelligent Bridge.\" I\'m also planning bullet-points with subtle micro-animations that show actual track automations. A key element is the interactive \"TRIGGER PLUG-IN SIMULATOR\" CTA, which will scroll to the DAW widget or highlight the floating chat plugin. The plan is to structure the homepage as full screen, allowing the user to scroll into Docs, About, and Support sections. I am also implementing the scroll depth observer.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 22
      nanos: 450852050
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
