  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Confirming Success and Scope**\n\nI\'m incredibly pleased to report a successful build! The precision achieved on this first attempt is impressive. I\'m now conducting a final review to ensure our objectives are met. Specifically, I\'m checking the completeness of creating a website tailored for ALAN, your custom Ableton solution.\n\n\n**Showcasing ALAN\'s Abilities**\n\nI\'ve been deeply immersed in showcasing ALAN\'s functionality. The interactive DAW simulator is performing beautifully! Users can now input custom text prompts or click preset commands and see real-time track, automation, and waveform reactions within Ableton. We\'ve captured this, along with the futuristic dark-themed website with glowing accents and smooth animations. We\'re now refining the detailed visuals of each element!\n\n\n**Refining User Experience**\n\nI\'m now integrating active playhead cycles, peak VU meters, and toggle states. I\'m also ensuring the visuals of the plugin windows maintain a clean, high-fidelity aesthetic, akin to teenage engineering designs. The homepage will be interactive, filling the screen with elements that dynamically change as the user scrolls, including a telemetry counter and navigation updates.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the futuristic website for **ALAN**, your custom Ableton Live AI assistant plugin. The application compiles perfectly, featuring a high-contrast dark visual identity, neon glowing indicators, and a highly interactive real-time DAW simulator.\n\nHere is an overview of the design concepts and interactive systems designed for the landing page:\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual Identity & Cybernetic Theme\n* **Obsidian Slate Ambiance**: Designed on a deep obsidian canvas (`#090A0F`) containing laser-sharp cyber grid tracking lines and responsive, glowing border edges.\n* **Ambient Radial Aura**: Added absolute background radial gradients that morph and slide dynamically between **Neon Emerald**, **Cyan**, and **Amethyst Purple** shadows as the user navigates sections.\n* **Scrolled telemetry HUD**: Implemented an absolute-positioned floating producer dashboard on the screen margin. This HUD tracks the exact vertical scroll coordinate (e.g., `00.0%` to `100.0%`) and project tempo in real-time.\n* **Aesthetic Pairings**: Headings pair sleek, heavy Display typography with high-precision `JetBrains Mono` character alignments for telemetry structures and server statuses.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\216\233\357\270\217 Interactive Modules & Pages\n\n#### 1. Page 1: ALAN (The Homepage VST Simulator)\n* Presides over a full-screen layout. Centered on the right is a fully-styled, pixel-perfect **Ableton Live Arrangement Timeline & Mixer Board** paired with the **ALAN AI Floating VST Panel**.\n* **Real-time DAW Reactions**: Users can click preset telemetry commands or type custom prompts into the chat box. Once dispatched, ALAN responds with logical, multi-step producer logs, and the **DAW timeline actively mutates**:\n  * **Quantize Synth MIDI**: Shits MIDI note rectangles into rigid grid alignments, flashing green.\n  * **Configure Sidechain Ducking**: Introduces a running sine-wave automation lane overlay on the bass channel with pulsating VU level meters.\n  * **Insert Atmospheric Reverb**: Triggers a deep purple floating aura around the vocal channel and displays active wet/dry faders.\n  * **Global BPM Acceleration**: Ramps the global transport clock up to `138.00 BPM` digit-by-digit, accelerating timelines.\n  * **Interactive Custom Input Heuristic**: Users can type any prompt (e.g., *\"give me vocal decay\"* or *\"shift grid\"*) to trigger realistic terminal output sequences.\n\n#### 2. Page 2: Documentation (Telemetry Library)\n* Organized under a technical left-sidebar filter. Producers can select diverse categories (*Getting Started*, *MIDI Alignment*, *Parameter Automation*, and *VST API Insertion*).\n* Includes a **Click-to-Fly Gateway**: Clicking any documentation code blocks instantly copies that prompt, flies the page scroll smoothly upward to the main VST Simulator, and triggers the live automation sequence.\n\n#### 3. Page 3: Technology Engine (About)\n* Showcases the underlying infrastructure behind ALAN in a pristine bento grid configuration.\n* Details the Rust/C++ MaxForLive API bridge latency, LLM musical grammar transformers, generative modal scales library, and digital signal path routing systems.\n\n#### 4. Page 4: Support Console (Telemetry Upload)\n* Connects a glassmorphic support ticket submission form with a **Live Terminal Log Screen** on the right side.\n* Submitting queries runs a secure terminal packaging simulation sequence, typing out connection handshakes, RSA encryption segments, and assigned ticket IDs.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 58
      nanos: 94144162
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
